<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-02T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="1146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1146">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BTH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Birch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-02T11:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 2, 1915, 11 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. Your telegram unnumbered, August 30, 5 p. m. Portuguese Government
                            has not embargoed arms and ammunition. Would be negligible factor.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BTH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Birch</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>